Program: Outlook
Title: Ferry Safety
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbrty
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
A look at ferry safety in Cameroon in the wake of the al-Salam Boccaccio 98 ferry disaster. Also, Hungarian actor and theatre director Peter Halasz talks about being terminally ill; Rajesh Thind on man's tribal mind and perceptions of appearance. Presenter: Frederick Dove.